  "title": "The Importance of Play in Learning in Practice: Exploring Emotional Benefits of Playful Interaction",
  "lessonText": "Play is essential for emotional development and social interaction.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• Play fosters emotional resilience and helps youth express feelings.\n• Engaging in playful interactions promotes social skills and teamwork.\n• Through play, youth learn to navigate challenges and build confidence.\n• Emotional benefits include reduced stress and improved mood.\n• Playful learning environments encourage creativity and imagination, as discussed in the Foundations of The Importance of Play in Learning."
  }
}
